# Cursor cold-start alignment (K-HARDEN-8)

This project uses a **cross-agent harness**. Cursor must follow the canonical
agent contract documented in `AGENTS.md`, identical to what Claude Code,
Codex CLI, Gemini CLI, and Aider follow.

## Read order (in priority)

1. `AGENTS.md` — canonical shared agent contract (HIGHEST priority)
2. `HARNESS_PLAYBOOK.md` — full operating manual
3. `skills/SUBAGENT_HARNESS.md` — subagent dispatch template (if applicable)
4. `constitution.md` — axiom layer

## Hard rules (enforced mechanically)

- **PR-only workflow**: never `git push origin main`. Always create a feature
  branch (`git checkout -b feat/whatever origin/main`) and push to it. Open
  a PR with `gh pr create`. Direct push blocked by:
  - GitHub server-side branch protection (universal)
  - Local git pre-push hook (`scripts/hooks/pre-push.harden`)
- **No wildcard staging**: never use `git add .`, `git add -A`, or
  `git add --all`. Use explicit file paths. Enforced at pre-commit layer.
- **No sidecar contamination**: never stage files under
  `handover/evidence/dev_self_hosting/dev_*/` or `.claude/worktrees/`.
- **Restricted surfaces** (see `AGENTS.md` §6): touching `src/kernel.rs`,
  `src/state/sequencer.rs`, `src/state/typed_tx.rs`, `constitution.md`,
  `rules/engine.py`, etc. requires per-atom architect §8 sign-off.

## Coding style

Two skill files document the discipline:
- `skills/KARPATHY_ARCHITECT.md` — first-principles architecture, monolithic-flat
- `skills/KARPATHY_SIMPLE_CODE.md` — transparent data flow, no Manager/Factory/Engine

## Setup (one time per clone)

```bash
bash scripts/install_hooks.sh
bash scripts/setup_branch_protection.sh   # admin only
```

## Verification (cold-start sanity)

```bash
bash scripts/run_constitution_gates.sh
cargo test --test constitution_subagent_pr_hygiene
```

## Conflict resolution

If any rule here contradicts `AGENTS.md`, `AGENTS.md` wins. This file exists
only because Cursor's auto-discovery prefers `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`.
